  "Ah, I'm gonna ask Mona about it."

  "Right! He's Narumi-san's dad too. Once you're done, share the results to me please!"

  "Okay! I'm gonna message her right now."

  _"If this suspicion is true, then her family is really stacked..."_

  Uta navigated to her messaging thread with Mona. Compared to the thread she's
  just talked on, this one was much, much shorter. Well, Uta did not have much
  to talk about with Mona, and to be fair, they mostly interacted at school,
  rather than through a messaging app.

  At least now there would be a topic for her to strike a new conversation. She
  forwarded the announcement picture before sending a message,

  "Mona! Is this really your dad?"

  Briefly after, the status of her message changed from 'Sent' to have been
  'Seen'.

  _"She saw it..."_

  Knowing Mona, Uta knew that it would be a while until she would get a proper
  answer. Well, she did not have any problem with it, as it is not some urgent
  matter or anything like that.

  Right then, a message was announced on the train.

